            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A soft suspension leaves your listing visible on Google Maps but you lose edit access — you cannot respond to reviews, update hours, or publish posts. A hard suspension removes the listing entirely from Google Maps and local search results.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the most common cause of GBP suspension?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Business name violations top the list. Adding keywords, city names, or descriptors to your business name field instead of using your exact legal business name is the single most common trigger for suspension.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can competitors get my listing suspended?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Competitors can report your listing for guideline violations. If your listing is fully compliant, reports are unlikely to trigger a suspension. Non-compliant listings — keyword-stuffed names, incorrect addresses — are more vulnerable to competitor reports being actioned.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
